#### 2a. Check Sum Parity
Iterate $i$ from $0$ to $N-1$. If the $i$-th bit of $M$ is set, add $\text{nums}[i]$ to the sum, or just XOR $\text{nums}[i]$ into a parity tracker.
The sum is even if the parity is 0.

#### 2b. Check Connectivity
The induced subgraph $G[S]$ must be connected.

We can use Breadth-First Search (BFS) or Depth-First Search (DFS) starting from any node in $S$ to check connectivity.

1. Pick an arbitrary starting node $r \in S$ (e.g., the node corresponding to the least significant bit set in $M$).
2. Perform a traversal (BFS/DFS) restricted only to nodes in $S$ and edges between nodes in $S$.
3. Count how many nodes in $S$ were visited.
4. If the count equals the total number of nodes in $S$ (which is the number of set bits in $M$), the subgraph is connected.

